<p>Since 1984, Conservation Services Group (CSG) has pioneered promoting energy efficiency, conservation, and clean energy technologies that are helping consumers save money as well as protecting the environment. CSG and its affiliated contractors perform more than 500,000 energy audits and assessments a year.  CSG uses a range of proprietary technologies to help run high-volume programs, estimate savings and advance the measurement of building performance standards. .

<p>
CSG pioneered the first portable audit tool to evaluate residential energy efficiency in the mid 1980's. In 2009, CSG turned to Nevo to develop the latest, most advanced tool for that purpose.  EnergyMeasure Home allows CSG's staff and affiliated auditors to capture every conceivable detail of an home's construction and configuration, model the energy consumption, adjust for seasonal and location-specific variations, reconcile the predicted results with actual energy bills, and make detailed recommendations for actions. EnergyMeasure Home covers the entire workflow from audit, through installation, to quality control inspections.  It works for home energy scoring, direct installs, simple improvement projects and complex, deep retrofits.  EnergyMeasure Home combines CSG's expertise in field operations, applied building science and program design for large-scale energy efficiency programs and is based on
established national standards (e.g., the EPA's carbon footprint algorithm and protocols).
<div style="margin-top: 8px;"></div>
The technical challenges for this project were particularly complex. And, like all Nevo projects, it needed to be delivered on time, within a set of strict budgetary constraints.
<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Requirements</font>

<p>CSG engaged Nevo to:
<ul>
<li>Capture detailed requirements for the new EnergyMeasure Home energy audit tool.
</li><li>Develop reliable estimates for the project duration and cost, despite the expectation that requirements would evolve as the system was implemented.
</li><li>Architect and design a solution that would provide the flexibility and extensibility required for the projected growth.
</li><li>Provide an implementation that could work without any network access.
</li><li>Incorporate a very high level of flexibility and configurability, recognizing that energy conservation programs, building practices, not to mention weather, vary enormously from location to location.
</li><li>Support extremely complex, and highly variable engineering algorithms.
</li>
</ul>

<font class="sectionTitleText">Nevo's Solution</font>

<p>Nevo spent several months reviewing the existing application, speaking with users, and interviewing a cross section of CSG staff to capture a detailed description of requirements.  Nevo's project estimation process defines use cases at relatively fine level of detail, and then engages the technical team to produces remarkably reliable estimates, including a measure of uncertainty that was used to finalize the project budget.

<div style="margin-top: 8px;"></div>
Nevo selected Microsoft's .NET platform for the new EnergyMeasure Home, and implemented a full suite of project tools including source control, issue tracking, a project WIKI for collaboration, and a continuous integration server.
<div style="margin-top: 8px;"></div>
We designed a solution that includes a centralized, server-based data repository, with local databases that are synchronized and replicated when the applications detects network availability.  This allows the user to experience the full range of functionality whether or not a connection can be made.
<p>CSG announced the release of EnergyMeasure Home in May of 2011, and is now rolling it out to programs across the country.

